HEADWORD: acne
<hw>ac"ne</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧k"n⟦esl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., prob.
a corruption of Gr. <grk>'akmh`</grk>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>Inflammation of the sebaceous glands that are associated with hair
follicles, leading to visible comedones and pimples, especially on the
face, back, and chest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>AS</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acnodal</ent>⟦br⟧
